transcript.text: Hello and welcome to on print Shop.
Here in this video we will see our new feature third party shipment billing that is launch in version 7.2.
This feature allows you to configure a third party like FedEx and UPS for shipping payments and not always the admin.
You can configure the shipment account details for the retail customers, corporates or corporate customers and have the shipment amount billed from their account directly.
So to enable third party shipment billing, firstly we need to go to store configuration, then shipping method, then go to UPS or FedEx shipping method.
Under the edit section, we'll find the third party billing option.
After this you will see an option named Third party billing shipping incorporate.
You get the option to configure it corporate wise or customer wise.
Select the shipping method from drop down and enter the account details.
So now let's see how it works on front end.
Now when a corporate customer logs into their account, the shipping amount of UPS will be kept hidden from them at the checkout page as it will be directly billed to the corporates UPS account.
If you have any queries, please e-mail us at support at on printshop.com.
